## Authentication

<!-- {{#if tauri}} -->
### Desktop Authentication

**Method**: Not applicable (single-user desktop app)

If cloud sync enabled (tauri-aws), see Cloud Authentication section.
<!-- {{/if}} -->

<!-- {{#if nextjs-aws}} -->
### Authentication Method

**Type**: {{authMethod}}

**Login Flow**:
```http
POST /api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "password": "secure_password"
}
```

**Response**:
```json
{
  "token": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIs...",
  "user": {
    "id": "uuid",
    "email": "user@example.com",
    "name": "User Name"
  },
  "expiresIn": 3600
}
```

**Subsequent Requests**:
```http
GET /api/resource
Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIs...
```
<!-- {{/if}} -->

<!-- {{#if tauri-aws}} -->
### Cloud Authentication

**Method**: {{authMethod}}

Desktop app stores token securely in OS keychain after cloud login.

**Token Refresh**:
```typescript
// Auto-refresh before expiry
if (tokenExpiresIn < 5 * 60 * 1000) {
  await refreshToken();
}
```
<!-- {{/if}} -->

## API Endpoints

<!-- {{#if tauri}} -->
### Tauri Commands

#### Get User Profile

```rust
#[tauri::command]
async fn get_user(id: String, state: State<'_, AppState>) -> Result<User, String> {
    let user = state.db.get_user(&id).await
        .map_err(|e| e.to_string())?;
    Ok(user)
}
```

**Frontend Usage**:
```typescript
import { invoke } from '@tauri-apps/api/tauri';

const user = await invoke<User>('get_user', { id: '123' });
```

